Intuition
The rating of a device is the minimum capacity among its units.

If we choose a device as a source, the best unit to remove is always its smallest unit because:

Removing any other unit does not increase the device's rating.
Removing the smallest unit changes the rating from the smallest element to the second smallest element.
Therefore, for every device we only care about:

mn1 = smallest element
mn2 = second smallest element
Suppose every device contributes its second smallest element (mn2) to the answer, meaning we remove the minimum from every device.

However, all removed minimum elements must be transferred somewhere. To maximize the final sum, they should all be transferred to the device having the globally smallest minimum (minm), since adding elements to that device does not decrease its rating.

As a result, one device contributes its smallest element (minm) instead of its second smallest element. To maximize the answer, we replace the smallest second minimum (sminm) with the global minimum (minm).

This gives the formula:

answer = minm + (sum of all second minimums) - sminm

Approach
Handle the special case when there is only one device.

If every device contains exactly one unit, no beneficial transfer is possible, so return the sum of all ratings.

For each device:

Find its smallest element (mn1).
Find its second smallest element (mn2).
Add mn2 to the running sum.
Maintain:
minm = global minimum among all mn1
sminm = minimum among all mn2
Return:

minm + sum - sminm

Code
class Solution {
public:
    long long maxRatings(vector<vector<int>>& units) {
          int n=units.size();
        if(n==1)return *min_element(units[0].begin(),units[0].end());
        long long sum=0;
        bool flag=true;
        for(auto&it:units){
            if(it.size()==1)sum+=it[0];
            else{
                flag=false;
                break;
            }
        }
        if(flag)return sum;
        sum=0;
        int minm=INT_MAX,sminm=INT_MAX;
        for(auto& it:units){
            int mn1=INT_MAX,mn2=INT_MAX;
            for(int x:it){
                if(x<mn1){
                    mn2=mn1;
                    mn1=x;
                }
                else if(x<mn2){
                    mn2=x;
                }
            }
            sum+=mn2;
            minm=min(minm,mn1);
            sminm=min(sminm,mn2);
        }
        return minm+sum-sminm;
    }
};
